WEBVTT

00:03.837 --> 00:07.131
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
CARSEY-WERNER
AND FOX BROADCASTING

00:13.138 --> 00:14.555
OH, UM, HERE, BERNICE.

00:14.723 --> 00:16.181
I MADE YOU
A PLATE OF LEFTOVERS.

00:16.349 --> 00:18.684
OH, THANK YOU...
THAT REMINDS ME, RED.

00:18.852 --> 00:21.729
MY GARBAGE DISPOSAL
IS STILL BROKEN.

00:23.023 --> 00:25.399
WELL, JUST AS LONG
AS YOU ENJOY IT.

00:25.567 --> 00:28.402
LISTEN, I'VE GOT AN IDEA.
LET'S EAT OUT NEXT SUNDAY.

00:28.570 --> 00:32.239
THAT WAY, EVERYBODY CAN GET
SOMETHING THEY LIKE.

00:33.366 --> 00:35.617
OKAY, GRANDMA,
TIME TO GET YOU HOME.

00:36.703 --> 00:39.371
ERIC, YOU GOT TO WARM THAT CAR
UP FOR AT LEAST 10 MINUTES.

00:39.539 --> 00:40.372
HE'S A GOOD BOY.

00:40.540 --> 00:43.000
IT'S JUST A SHAME HE DOESN'T
HAVE A BETTER HOME LIFE.

00:45.712 --> 00:48.464
AH. YOU KNOW, KITTY,
WHEN I WAS RAISING CHILDREN,

00:48.631 --> 00:50.215
THE RIGHT WAY...

00:56.973 --> 00:58.182
THAT'S WARM ENOUGH, ERIC.

00:58.349 --> 00:59.600
BUT YOU JUST...
SHOW ME TAILLIGHTS.

00:59.768 --> 01:01.226
LET'S ROLL, GRANDMA.

01:01.394 --> 01:05.230
[MANDY PLAYS SOFTLY ON RADIO]

01:05.398 --> 01:07.024
[TURNS UP VOLUME]

01:07.192 --> 01:11.320
TURN OFF
THAT BEATNIK MUSIC.

01:11.488 --> 01:13.697
WATCH THE ROAD.

01:16.868 --> 01:18.577
YOU DON'T LIKE IT
WHEN I COME TO VISIT.

01:18.745 --> 01:19.912
YES, I DO.
I REALLY DO.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.122
YOU'RE A FILTHY LIAR.

01:22.540 --> 01:24.291
YOU DIDN'T LEARN TO LIE
FROM MY RED.

01:24.459 --> 01:27.086
THAT CAME FROM YOUR MOTHER.

01:27.253 --> 01:30.089
YOU SEE, GRANDMA, THAT'S
THE PROBLEM RIGHT THERE, OKAY?

01:30.256 --> 01:32.132
EVERY TIME YOU COME
TO MY HOUSE,

01:32.300 --> 01:34.093
YOU SPEND THE WHOLE DAY
CRITICIZING MY MOM.

01:34.260 --> 01:35.761
WELL, I TELL IT
LIKE IT IS.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.763
OKAY, GRANDMA,
THEN HERE'S HOW IT IS.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.473
YOU'RE VERY NASTY.

01:39.641 --> 01:42.309
AND I DON'T SEE WHY YOU
HAVE TO BE SO HATEFUL.

01:42.477 --> 01:46.021
I DON'T THINK BEING NICE
FOR A WHOLE DAY WOULD KILL YOU.

01:49.651 --> 01:52.152
GRANDMA?

01:52.320 --> 01:54.321
[BUMP]

01:55.824 --> 01:58.575
GRANDMA?

01:58.743 --> 02:00.702
OH... OH, NO!

02:09.796 --> 02:11.672
HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:11.840 --> 02:13.006
JUST SHOOTIN'
SOME HOOPS.

02:13.174 --> 02:15.509
OH, I'LL GET IT.

02:15.677 --> 02:18.512
ERIC, WHAT'S YOUR GRANDMA
DOING SLEEPING IN THE CAR?

02:21.641 --> 02:23.600
SHE'S NOT, UH,
SHE'S NOT SLEEPING.

02:23.768 --> 02:25.853
SHE'S DEAD.

02:27.605 --> 02:28.814
NO. REALLY.
SHE'S DEAD.

02:28.982 --> 02:31.441
[SHUDDERS]
WH-WHAT?!

02:31.609 --> 02:33.944
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT, SHE'S DEAD?!

02:34.112 --> 02:37.281
I, UH, WAS DRIVING HER HOME,
AND THEN I YELLED AT HER,

02:37.448 --> 02:40.325
AND THEN SHE DIED.

02:40.493 --> 02:42.494
SHE DIED?!
WELL, WHAT DID RED SAY?

02:42.662 --> 02:45.414
OH, I'M NOT TELLING RED.

02:45.582 --> 02:47.416
UM, ERIC, I DON'T
MEAN TO CRITICIZE,

02:47.584 --> 02:50.043
BUT ARE YOU INSANE?!
YOU NEED TO DO SOMETHING!

02:50.211 --> 02:52.171
ERIC, I JUST GOT TO GET
MY 8-TRACK OUT OF THE CAR.

02:52.338 --> 02:53.839
KELSO...

02:54.007 --> 02:54.673
GRANDMA FORMAN,

02:54.841 --> 02:57.217
CAN YOU JUST MOVE
YOUR LEG A LITTLE BIT?

02:57.844 --> 02:59.720
KELSO, SHE'S DEAD.

02:59.888 --> 03:04.516
[SHUDDERS]

03:04.684 --> 03:07.394
OH, MY GOD!

03:13.318 --> 03:14.568
ERIC, YOU'RE IN SHOCK.

03:14.736 --> 03:16.862
YOU HAVE TO GO INSIDE AND TELL
RED RIGHT NOW, RIGHT NOW!

03:17.030 --> 03:18.780
WAIT, UM...

03:18.948 --> 03:20.240
WILL YOU DO IT?

03:20.408 --> 03:23.493
PLEASE!
RIGHT NOW!

03:25.830 --> 03:27.497
OH.

03:27.665 --> 03:30.334
I FORGOT THE TUPPERWARE.

03:39.844 --> 03:41.720
OH! SHE SENT BACK
THE LEFTOVERS.

03:41.888 --> 03:43.347
THIS IS SO TYPICAL
OF YOUR GRANDMOTHER.

03:43.514 --> 03:46.475
WHY DO I EVEN
PUT UP WITH HER?

03:46.643 --> 03:47.976
MOM, I THINK YOU MIGHT BE
COMING DOWN A LITTLE HARD

03:48.144 --> 03:50.812
ON GRANDMA THIS TIME.

03:50.980 --> 03:51.480
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:51.648 --> 03:55.984
SHE IS JUST AN EVIL, EVIL,
HORRIBLE LITTLE WOMAN.

03:56.152 --> 03:58.028
WHAT DID SHE SAY
ABOUT ME THIS TIME?

03:58.196 --> 04:00.822
NOT MUCH.

04:00.990 --> 04:02.866
SO DID YOU GET
YOUR GRANDMA HOME OKAY?

04:08.498 --> 04:10.666
WELL, UM...

04:10.833 --> 04:13.085
YOU KNOW, THE STRANGEST
THING HAPPENED.

04:16.547 --> 04:20.968
OKAY, NOW HERE'S THE PART
WHERE I GET LOST.

04:21.135 --> 04:23.553
HOW DID SHE HIT
THE SIDEWALK?

04:23.721 --> 04:25.180
WELL, I OPENED
THE DOOR FOR HER.

04:25.348 --> 04:26.390
AND WHAT THE HELL
WAS GOING THROUGH YOUR HEAD

04:26.557 --> 04:27.432
WHEN YOU DID THAT?!

04:27.600 --> 04:28.558
OH, JUST YELL AT HIM, RED.

04:28.726 --> 04:32.187
I'M SURE THAT HIS GRANDMOTHER
DYING HASN'T UPSET HIM ENOUGH.

04:32.355 --> 04:33.313
ERIC, TAKE YOUR MOTHER
IN THE HOUSE.

04:33.481 --> 04:35.941
SHE'S HYSTERICAL.

04:37.068 --> 04:37.818
YES, SIR.

04:37.986 --> 04:39.903
AND, UM, I HAVE
TO TELL YOU, SIR,

04:40.071 --> 04:42.114
WHEN WE WERE DRIVING,
I SAID TO GRANDMA...

04:42.282 --> 04:43.323
I SAID...

04:43.491 --> 04:45.951
ERIC! THIS IS NO TIME
TO GET UPSET!

04:46.119 --> 04:49.830
WELL, WHEN IS
THE RIGHT TIME?

04:49.998 --> 04:50.747
I'LL HANDLE THIS, ERIC.

04:50.915 --> 04:52.749
YOU JUST TAKE
YOUR MOTHER IN THE HOUSE.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.419
MOM.

04:55.586 --> 04:59.381
WELL, TH-THIS IS...
THIS IS A TERRIBLE LOSS.

05:02.135 --> 05:05.846
MOM, DIDN'T YOU JUST SAY
THAT SHE WAS EVIL?

05:06.014 --> 05:08.473
I NEVER SAID
ANY SUCH THING.

05:10.727 --> 05:12.686
OKAY.

05:12.854 --> 05:14.438
[THUD]

05:27.577 --> 05:30.537
OH, SWEETIE,
I AM SO GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

05:30.705 --> 05:33.081
YEAH. I HAD A FINAL
THIS WEEK.

05:33.249 --> 05:35.125
OH, I'M SO SORRY, HONEY.

05:35.293 --> 05:36.752
OH, NO. THIS COULDN'T HAVE COME
AT A BETTER TIME.

05:36.919 --> 05:39.296
I WAS REALLY UNPREPARED.

05:41.841 --> 05:45.427
BUT I MISS GRANDMA.

05:45.595 --> 05:48.388
I KNOW, HONEY.
WE ALL DO.

05:49.932 --> 05:52.017
MOM, WHAT IS
WITH ALL THIS FOOD?

05:52.185 --> 05:56.229
WELL, YOU KNOW, BUSY HANDS
ARE HAPPY HANDS.

05:56.397 --> 06:01.568
OH, SAY, WOULD YOU LIKE A CUP
OF CHILI WITH YOUR WAFFLES?

06:01.736 --> 06:03.737
WELL, I DON'T KNOW...

06:03.905 --> 06:05.822
SURE!

06:08.701 --> 06:11.328
SO HOW DID YOUR BROTHER
TAKE THE NEWS?

06:11.496 --> 06:12.454
OH, YOU KNOW MARTY.

06:12.622 --> 06:13.872
HE'S TALKING
ABOUT HIS FEELINGS,

06:14.040 --> 06:15.123
AND THEN
HE STARTED BAWLING,

06:15.291 --> 06:17.250
SO I HUNG UP ON HIM.

06:19.212 --> 06:21.088
I'M NOT PAYING
LONG-DISTANCE RATES

06:21.255 --> 06:23.548
TO LISTEN TO THAT CRAP.

06:24.634 --> 06:26.593
UNCLE MARTY IS SO IN TOUCH
WITH HIS FEELINGS.

06:26.761 --> 06:29.596
IT'S LIKE HE'S COMPLETELY
SELF-ACTUALIZED.

06:29.764 --> 06:31.932
HE'S A DUMB-ASS.

06:33.851 --> 06:35.310
NOW, RED, HONEY,

06:35.478 --> 06:37.562
I DON'T THINK THAT
YOU'RE REALLY MAD AT MARTY.

06:37.730 --> 06:38.897
I THINK YOU ARE
JUST GOING THROUGH

06:39.065 --> 06:42.025
ONE OF THE FIVE STAGES
OF DEALING WITH DEATH.

06:43.236 --> 06:45.487
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

06:45.655 --> 06:47.572
THERE ARE FIVE STAGES:

06:47.740 --> 06:53.161
DENIAL, ANGER, BARGAINING,
DEPRESSION, ACCEPTANCE.

06:53.329 --> 06:56.415
KITTY, I'VE GOT 2 STAGES:

06:56.582 --> 06:59.543
ANGER AND DRINKING.

07:03.798 --> 07:05.257
ERIC, I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU SAID
TO YOUR GRANDMOTHER.

07:05.425 --> 07:07.426
YOU DID NOT KILL HER.

07:07.593 --> 07:09.428
I DID, DONNA.
I KILLED HER.

07:09.595 --> 07:11.471
SHE WAS OLD, AND THE SHOCK
OF HER GRANDSON

07:11.639 --> 07:15.725
TELLING HER
THAT SHE WAS NASTY KILLED HER.

07:15.893 --> 07:17.269
HAVE YOU TALKED
TO RED ABOUT THIS?

07:17.437 --> 07:19.146
I'M NOT TALKING
TO MY DAD ABOUT THIS!

07:19.313 --> 07:19.855
DO YOU REMEMBER
HOW ANGRY HE GOT

07:20.022 --> 07:20.814
WHEN I DIDN'T RAKE THE YARD?

07:20.982 --> 07:23.275
AND THIS IS, LIKE,
TWICE AS BAD!

07:24.444 --> 07:26.319
WELL, I DON'T REALLY WANNA TALK
ABOUT THIS ANYMORE.

07:26.487 --> 07:28.822
ERIC, YOU NEED
TO TALK ABOUT THIS!

07:28.990 --> 07:32.367
DONNA, WE DON'T TALK ABOUT
THINGS IN THE FORMAN FAMILY.

07:32.535 --> 07:33.285
IT'S NOT
LIKE YOUR HOUSE,

07:33.453 --> 07:34.744
WHERE EVERY TIME
YOU HAVE A "FEELING,"

07:34.912 --> 07:37.956
YOUR DAD GIVES YOU
A BIG HUG AND A GOLD STAR.

07:38.124 --> 07:39.499
I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP YOU HERE.

07:39.667 --> 07:42.836
WELL, I DON'T... TALKING
ISN'T GONNA HELP ME, OKAY?!

07:43.004 --> 07:46.590
WHAT'S GONNA HELP ME
IS... DRINKING!

07:48.384 --> 07:50.844
WELL, NOW YOU'RE
JUST BEING STUPID.

07:51.971 --> 07:54.639
HEY, FORMAN,
LET'S GO GET WASTED.

07:54.807 --> 07:57.392
OH, GREAT.

07:57.935 --> 08:00.312
SEE?
HYDE'S A REAL FRIEND.

08:00.480 --> 08:04.107
HE'S GONNA HELP ME GET
THROUGH MY GRANDMA'S DEATH.

08:04.275 --> 08:07.819
YOUR GRANDMA'S DEAD?

08:07.987 --> 08:11.281
OH, MAN, UH...

08:11.449 --> 08:13.867
LET'S GO GET WASTED.

08:18.998 --> 08:20.665
AS FELLOW HUMAN BEINGS,

08:20.833 --> 08:24.127
NOT BROTHERS...
HUMAN BEINGS,

08:24.295 --> 08:28.256
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

08:28.424 --> 08:30.759
WHAT THE HELL
IS WRONG WITH YOU?

08:30.927 --> 08:34.012
I GOT AWAY FROM THIS FAMILY.
I'M NOT AFRAID OF MY FEELINGS.

08:34.597 --> 08:37.557
WELL, I AM.

08:37.725 --> 08:38.892
OKAY, NOW.

08:39.060 --> 08:41.520
WHO WOULD LIKE
A MONTE CRISTO?

08:41.687 --> 08:43.355
OH, KITTY,
GROOVY SANDWICHES.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.523
NO RED MEAT, RIGHT?

08:44.690 --> 08:45.440
OH, NO.

08:45.608 --> 08:47.359
JUST HAM.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.863
YOU KNOW, MARTY, WE REALLY
SHOULD TALK ABOUT MA'S FUNERAL.

08:52.031 --> 08:55.200
NO, DON'T WORRY.
IT'S ON ME.

08:55.368 --> 08:57.494
IT'S NOT
A ROUND OF BEERS.

08:57.662 --> 08:58.745
WE'LL SPLIT THE COST.

08:58.913 --> 09:02.249
SWEET RED.
SO GENEROUS.

09:02.416 --> 09:05.544
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE
LOW ON FUNDS.

09:05.711 --> 09:08.547
I JUST WANT
WHAT'S BEST FOR MOM.

09:08.714 --> 09:11.841
[WHIMPERING]

09:12.009 --> 09:14.970
YEAH, MARTY, THAT'S...
THAT'S WHAT WE ALL WANT.

09:15.137 --> 09:17.806
IT'S JUST THAT
WHEN I FEEL BAD,

09:17.974 --> 09:20.141
I DON'T CRY
LIKE A LITTLE GIRL.

09:20.309 --> 09:23.478
[BLUBBERING]

09:24.647 --> 09:26.231
WAITRESS...

09:26.440 --> 09:27.983
WAITRESS!

09:28.150 --> 09:32.445
FORMAN, RELAX, OKAY?

09:32.613 --> 09:35.156
HI. UH,
WE'RE GONNA NEED A PITCHER

09:35.324 --> 09:37.617
AND FOUR GLASSES, PLEASE.

09:37.785 --> 09:39.744
I'M GONNA NEED
TO SEE SOME I.D.

09:39.912 --> 09:41.830
OF COURSE.
I HAVE MINE RIGHT HERE,

09:41.998 --> 09:43.081
BUT THE REST
OF THE FELLAS LEFT THEIRS

09:43.249 --> 09:45.709
BACK AT THE MILITARY BASE.

09:46.419 --> 09:48.044
GOTCHA.

09:48.212 --> 09:51.089
UH, SO, YOU'RE
IN THE MILITARY?

09:51.257 --> 09:52.716
WHAT BASE
ARE YOU FROM?

09:52.883 --> 09:56.052
IT'S A SECRET MILITARY BASE.

09:56.220 --> 09:59.180
WELL, I'M CHARLOTTE,
AND THIS IS MY SISTER CHARLENE.

09:59.348 --> 10:02.559
HI. I'M... TED.

10:03.185 --> 10:06.479
SERGEANT SHAFT.

10:07.315 --> 10:10.108
I'M TOMMY HONCHO.

10:10.276 --> 10:13.945
I AM ERIC FORMAN.

10:14.113 --> 10:16.281
OH, UH, SALLY, UH,
PUT THAT ON OUR TAB.

10:16.449 --> 10:19.034
AND BRING EVERYBODY
A ROUND OF SHOTS.

10:19.201 --> 10:20.285
WHAT IS GOING ON?

10:20.453 --> 10:22.162
THEY'RE PICKING US UP.
AY, NO.

10:22.330 --> 10:23.288
NO. IT'S A GOOD THING.

10:23.456 --> 10:27.876
OH. OKAY.

10:28.044 --> 10:30.337
EXCUSE ME, FELLAS, BUT WE
NEED TO TALK TO THE LADIES.

10:30.963 --> 10:32.505
YEAH, WELL, THESE LADIES
ARE WITH US, OKAY?

10:32.673 --> 10:35.425
WELL, THEY CAME IN HERE
WITH US, OKAY? GREAT.

10:35.593 --> 10:39.596
GET LOST. THEY ARE
TRYING TO PICK US UP.

10:39.764 --> 10:42.432
I THINK YOU'VE HAD QUITE ENOUGH
FIREWATER, THERE, CHIEF.

10:42.600 --> 10:46.227
HEY, YOU MESS WITH ERIC FORMAN,
AND YOU MESS WITH ME.

10:47.897 --> 10:52.025
ARE YOU LOOKING
FOR TROUBLE?

10:52.193 --> 10:54.235
OH, YES.

10:54.403 --> 10:56.946
OH, I'M LOOKING
FOR TROUBLE.

11:00.826 --> 11:02.243
ANYBODY ELSE?

11:02.411 --> 11:03.995
HUH?

11:04.163 --> 11:06.373
WELL, THERE'S
THREE OF US, SO...

11:14.090 --> 11:17.050
SO WHERE WERE WE?

11:18.177 --> 11:21.221
OH, YES. YOU WERE
PICKING ME UP.

11:28.938 --> 11:29.896
WELL, NOW WHERE IS ERIC?

11:30.064 --> 11:32.816
IT'S 2 IN THE MORNING.
I'M WORRIED SICK.

11:32.983 --> 11:35.151
ERIC IS ACTING OUT.

11:35.319 --> 11:36.611
HE DOESN'T HAVE
THE EMOTIONAL TOOLS

11:36.779 --> 11:38.613
TO DEAL
WITH THIS TRAGEDY.

11:38.781 --> 11:43.118
YOU'RE AN EMOTIONAL TOOL,
MARTY.

11:43.285 --> 11:47.080
NOW, WHO WOULD LIKE
LEMON BUNDT CAKE?

11:49.542 --> 11:51.292
WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN?!

11:51.460 --> 11:54.045
UM, I WENT TO A BAR.

11:54.213 --> 11:56.506
ERIC, HAVE YOU
BEEN DRINKING?

11:56.674 --> 11:57.632
NO.
I'VE BEEN FIGHTING.

11:57.800 --> 12:00.218
OH, MY LORD!

12:00.386 --> 12:02.679
ERIC, IT'S OKAY.

12:02.847 --> 12:05.014
JUST LET
THE FEELINGS OUT.

12:05.182 --> 12:07.434
PUT 'EM BACK IN THERE, ERIC!

12:09.395 --> 12:11.062
YOU KNOW,
WHEN A FATHER AND SON...

12:11.230 --> 12:14.482
MARTY, YOU ARE THIS CLOSE
TO A HEADLOCK.

12:14.650 --> 12:16.651
GOOD NIGHT!

12:17.153 --> 12:19.070
ERIC, JUST BECAUSE
THERE HAS BEEN

12:19.238 --> 12:20.739
A TRAGEDY
IN THE FAMILY

12:20.906 --> 12:22.449
IS NO REASON
TO ACT CRAZY.

12:22.616 --> 12:24.659
MY SON GETTING
IN A BAR FIGHT,

12:24.827 --> 12:28.455
LIKE... LIKE SOME KIND
OF BAR FIGHTER!

12:30.750 --> 12:34.294
KITTY, STOP COOKING...

12:34.462 --> 12:37.922
AND GO TO BED.

12:38.090 --> 12:40.175
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

12:40.342 --> 12:42.010
WHEN THE TIMER GOES OFF,

12:42.178 --> 12:44.137
ONE OF YOU BETTER TAKE
THAT ROAST OUT OF THE OVEN,

12:44.305 --> 12:46.556
OR THERE WILL BE
HELL TO PAY.

12:49.101 --> 12:51.478
SIT DOWN, ERIC.

12:59.111 --> 13:01.446
DON'T DRINK THAT.

13:01.614 --> 13:05.366
PUT IT ON YOUR EYE.

13:05.534 --> 13:08.578
COME ON, I'M KIDDING!

13:17.963 --> 13:22.008
SO... THIS IS BEER.

13:31.227 --> 13:33.311
AND AS MUCH AS
WE ALL MISS BERNICE,

13:33.479 --> 13:37.607
WE MUST REMEMBER THAT SHE
IS NOW IN A FAR BETTER PLACE.

13:40.361 --> 13:42.195
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DIE TO GET
TO A BETTER PLACE, MAN.

13:42.363 --> 13:44.322
JUST DRIVE 50 MILES
IN ANY DIRECTION.

13:44.490 --> 13:46.199
SHUT UP, HYDE.

13:50.246 --> 13:51.996
ARE YOU OKAY?

13:52.164 --> 13:54.207
I DON'T KNOW, MICHAEL.

13:54.375 --> 13:58.002
IT'S JUST THAT...
DEATH IS SO UNEXPECTED.

13:58.170 --> 14:00.171
I MEAN, WE ARE
SUCH FRAGILE BEINGS,

14:00.339 --> 14:02.841
NEVER KNOWING WHEN
THE FLAME OF OUR LIVES

14:03.008 --> 14:05.927
WILL BE BLOWN OUT
BY THE WIND OF DEATH.

14:06.095 --> 14:07.846
WHAT?

14:08.931 --> 14:10.640
I AM SO TURNED ON!
AREN'T YOU?

14:10.808 --> 14:11.432
OKAY.
LET'S GO.

14:11.600 --> 14:12.308
CAR?
COAT ROOM.

14:12.476 --> 14:14.727
BETTER.

14:19.608 --> 14:24.195
Kitty:
UM... I KNOW
WE HAD OUR DIFFERENCES.

14:24.363 --> 14:27.115
I MARRIED RED, AND... AND... AND
YOU HATED ME.

14:27.283 --> 14:31.828
AHEM. UH, WELL, UH,
JUST TRY TO BE NICER TO GOD.

14:37.376 --> 14:39.627
Laurie:
LIFE IS SO
COMPLICATED.

14:39.795 --> 14:43.339
YOU GET OLD AND DIE.

14:43.507 --> 14:46.676
THANK GOD I'M STILL
YOUNG AND HOT.

14:52.892 --> 14:53.808
Hyde:
MAN, I CAN'T BELIEVE

14:53.976 --> 14:58.021
THEY'RE JUST GONNA
THROW THAT RING AWAY.

15:01.567 --> 15:04.068
ARGH! NO, I CAN'T!

15:07.364 --> 15:10.325
Fez: OH, MY GOD!
THERE IS A BODY IN HERE!

15:14.455 --> 15:16.623
Red:
WELL, MA...

15:16.790 --> 15:19.083
OH, FOR GOD'S SAKE!

15:22.338 --> 15:23.504
OH, SORRY.

15:23.672 --> 15:26.507
THOSE SHOULD BE CLOSED.

15:29.178 --> 15:33.306
HEY... OH, GOD!
YOU GOT A BLACK EYE.

15:33.474 --> 15:36.142
IT... LOOKS PRETTY HOT.

15:36.769 --> 15:38.811
WELL, YOU SHOULD
SEE THE OTHER GUY.

15:38.979 --> 15:40.688
DID YOU REALLY
LAY HIM OUT?

15:40.856 --> 15:42.023
NO.
I MEAN, HE WAS HUGE.

15:42.191 --> 15:44.525
I MEAN, YOU SHOULD HAVE...
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN HIM.

15:44.693 --> 15:45.777
THE FACT THAT
I EVEN TOOK THE PUNCH

15:45.945 --> 15:50.615
IS A TESTAMENT
TO HOW TOUGH I REALLY AM.

15:50.783 --> 15:51.491
OW.

15:51.659 --> 15:54.661
OH! SORRY.

15:57.122 --> 16:00.541
LOOK, DONNA, I'M SORRY.

16:00.709 --> 16:03.378
ABOUT THE OTHER NIGHT.
I WAS ACTING CRAZY.

16:03.545 --> 16:04.879
AND, UM...

16:05.047 --> 16:07.215
AND I'M COMPLETELY
OVER IT NOW.

16:07.383 --> 16:10.301
I MEAN, YOU JUST...
YOU CAN'T DWELL ON THESE THINGS.

16:10.469 --> 16:11.928
SO YOU HAD
A HEART-TO-HEART WITH RED?

16:12.096 --> 16:13.930
HELL, NO.

16:14.098 --> 16:16.224
SO YOU'RE STILL JUST
SUPPRESSING EVERYTHING.

16:16.392 --> 16:19.435
SURE BEATS DEALING
WITH IT NOW, RIGHT?

16:20.145 --> 16:22.230
HUG.

16:27.027 --> 16:30.488
I'M... REALLY SORRY
YOUR MOM DIED.

16:30.656 --> 16:33.700
IT'S LIKE...
SAD AND STUFF.

16:38.455 --> 16:41.165
HEY!

16:41.333 --> 16:43.418
PRETTY GREAT
FUNERAL, HUH?

16:48.465 --> 16:51.843
RED, I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOUR MOM, MAN.

16:52.011 --> 16:54.429
AND I'M SORRY
KELSO'S AN IDIOT.

16:59.476 --> 17:02.353
MR. RED...
ALWAYS REMEMBER,

17:02.521 --> 17:05.023
A MOTHER'S GOODNESS
IS CARRIED ON FOREVER

17:05.190 --> 17:07.025
BY HER SONS.

17:07.192 --> 17:15.700
[MARTY WHIMPERING]

17:15.868 --> 17:18.661
HAVE YOU MET
MY SISTER MARTY?

17:18.829 --> 17:21.080
[BLUBBERING]

17:22.875 --> 17:24.542
HEY, WHAT'S
ALL THIS STUFF?

17:24.710 --> 17:27.545
CAMERAS. MY DAD WAS
AN AMATEUR PHOTOGRAPHER.

17:27.713 --> 17:29.047
HAD HIS OWN DARKROOM.

17:29.214 --> 17:32.550
REALLY?

17:32.718 --> 17:34.927
HEY, FORMY, YOU HAVE ANY
NAKED PICTURES OF YOUR GRANDMA?

17:35.095 --> 17:36.763
NO!

17:36.930 --> 17:39.599
HA HA!
YOU DO NOW!

17:44.396 --> 17:48.399
HEY!
MY OLD TRAIN SET.

17:48.567 --> 17:50.151
YOUR TRAIN SET?

17:50.319 --> 17:52.153
THAT WAS OUR TRAIN SET.

17:52.321 --> 17:53.988
WELL, REALLY,
IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN MINE.

17:54.156 --> 17:56.491
YOU NEVER PLAYED
WITH IT, RIGHT?

17:57.618 --> 18:02.663
RED...

18:02.831 --> 18:05.416
DO YOU WANT
TO KEEP THE TRAINS?

18:05.584 --> 18:06.584
IF YOU DON'T WANT 'EM.

18:06.752 --> 18:08.753
NO,
IT'S NOT ABOUT ME.

18:08.921 --> 18:10.588
IT'S ABOUT
WHAT YOU WANT.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.882
MAKE AN HONEST DECLARATION
OF YOUR NEEDS.

18:13.050 --> 18:15.384
WOULD YOU CUT THE CRAP?!

18:15.552 --> 18:19.680
JUST SAY TO ME,
"MARTY, I WANT THE TRAINS."

18:22.518 --> 18:25.728
MARTY...

18:25.896 --> 18:28.564
I'D BE GLAD TO HANG ON
TO 'EM FOR YOU.

18:28.732 --> 18:30.066
RED... ARE YOU
ASKING ME FOR THEM?

18:30.234 --> 18:31.484
NO!

18:31.652 --> 18:33.069
FINE.

18:33.237 --> 18:35.571
THEN I'LL KEEP THEM.

18:35.739 --> 18:37.740
FINE.
GO AHEAD AND KEEP 'EM.

18:37.908 --> 18:40.243
I DON'T WANT
THE DAMN THINGS!

18:40.494 --> 18:41.953
KITTY...

18:42.121 --> 18:45.373
YOU GO IN THERE AND TELL THAT
BASTARD TO GIVE ME MY TRAINS!

18:49.128 --> 18:54.382
RED... IT'S YOUR PROBLEM.
I GOTTA MAKE A PIE.

19:15.320 --> 19:17.738
OH, WELL, NOW, SEE?

19:17.906 --> 19:19.949
MARTY LEFT YOU THE TRAINS.

19:20.117 --> 19:21.993
YEAH, HE DID.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.035
AND HE EVEN
SET IT UP RIGHT.

19:23.203 --> 19:25.204
SEE?
THE STATIONS ARE ALL SPREAD OUT.

19:25.372 --> 19:29.375
FIVE STOPS,
FIVE TIMES THE FUN.

19:29.543 --> 19:31.210
BUT IF HE THINKS HE'S PLAYING
WITH 'EM WHEN HE VISITS,

19:31.378 --> 19:33.546
HE'S GOT
ANOTHER THINK COMIN'.

19:33.714 --> 19:35.798
NOW, RED, YOU HAVE
TO SHARE WITH YOUR BROTHER.

19:35.966 --> 19:37.884
I DON'T WANNA!

19:38.427 --> 19:42.096
OKAY, I AM GONNA GO
MAKE A COFFEE CAKE.

19:42.264 --> 19:44.599
HA HA.
TOOT-TOOT!

19:47.895 --> 19:50.897
HEY, DAD, NICE TRAINS.

19:51.064 --> 19:53.858
YEAH.

19:54.026 --> 19:55.151
YOU KNOW,
I CAN'T BELIEVE

19:55.319 --> 19:56.903
THAT YOUR GRANDMA HELD ON
TO THEM ALL THESE YEARS.

19:57.070 --> 19:59.530
I THOUGHT SHE'D
THROWN 'EM AWAY.

19:59.698 --> 20:01.490
YEAH, SHE WAS A GOOD EGG,
GRANDMA.

20:01.658 --> 20:03.743
YEAH, SHE WAS.

20:03.911 --> 20:06.787
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS
A LITTLE BOY, I HATED PEACHES.

20:06.955 --> 20:11.000
AND MOM KNEW THAT, SO, UH,
WHENEVER SHE MADE A PEACH PIE,

20:11.168 --> 20:14.670
SHE'D MAKE A LITTLE
BLUEBERRY PIE... SPECIAL,

20:14.838 --> 20:17.590
JUST FOR ME.

20:17.758 --> 20:21.344
YOU KNOW, SHE WAS
THE FIRST ONE TO CALL ME RED.

20:21.511 --> 20:24.388
AND THE LAST TIME
I SAW HER...

20:24.556 --> 20:27.266
I DIDN'T...

20:27.434 --> 20:30.061
I DIDN'T SAY,
"I LOVE YOU."

20:30.229 --> 20:34.065
I DIDN'T EVEN
SAY GOOD-BYE.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.859
I SAID, "SHOW ME
THE TAILLIGHTS."

20:41.865 --> 20:45.743
DAD, UM, THE LAST THING
I SAID TO HER

20:45.911 --> 20:49.372
WAS, "IT WOULDN'T
KILL YOU TO BE NICE."

20:55.254 --> 20:58.798
BUT I THINK IT DID,
BECAUSE SHE DIED.

21:03.845 --> 21:07.807
THAT COULD ONLY
HAPPEN TO YOU, SON!

21:11.853 --> 21:13.980
IT'S OKAY.

21:14.147 --> 21:16.607
I KNOW.

21:25.158 --> 21:28.911
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
KITTY?

21:29.079 --> 21:33.416
I'M ALL OUT OF EGGS.

21:33.583 --> 21:36.252
AND FLOUR!

21:36.420 --> 21:37.586
[KITTY SOBBING]

21:37.754 --> 21:40.047
COME HERE.

21:40.215 --> 21:42.550
ERIC, COME HERE.

21:45.762 --> 21:48.931
HEY, DO YOU THINK
THESE DIAMONDS ARE REAL?

21:50.183 --> 21:51.809
OH, FAMILY MOMENT.

21:51.977 --> 21:54.312
I'LL LEAVE
YOU THREE ALONE.

21:57.691 --> 22:00.943
I'M JUST GONNA
WAIT OVER HERE.

22:02.863 --> 22:04.530
I'M REALLY SORRY
THAT OUR LAST CONVERSATION

22:04.698 --> 22:07.700
DIDN'T GO SO SMOOTH.

22:07.868 --> 22:11.287
BUT, UM, LOOK, THAT IS NOT
HOW I FEEL ABOUT YOU AT ALL.

22:11.455 --> 22:13.539
Voice imitating Bernice:
THEN WHY DID YOU KILL ME, ERIC?!

22:13.707 --> 22:16.542
I'LL NEVER FORGIVE YOU!

22:19.796 --> 22:23.049
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
DOING OUT HERE?

22:23.216 --> 22:26.010
FREEZING MY NADS OFF
FOR A JOKE, MAN.

22:26.261 --> 22:29.221
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
CARSEY-WERNER
AND FOX BROADCASTING
